datasource.query:
SELECT
	'',
	REGEXP_EXTRACT(labels, r'\|machine_type:(.*?)\|') AS machine_type,
	REGEXP_EXTRACT(labels, r'\|cloud:(.*?)\|') AS cloud,
	%%EXPRESSION%% AS number
FROM
	[{{ dataset_name }}.{{ table_name }}]
WHERE
	timestamp >= TIMESTAMP_TO_SEC(DATE_ADD(CURRENT_TIMESTAMP(), -3, 'MONTH')) AND
	product_name = 'PerfKitBenchmarker' AND
	test = 'block_storage_workload' AND
	metric = 'random_write:write:bandwidth' AND
    REGEXP_MATCH(labels, r'\|workload_mode:database\|') AND
    REGEXP_MATCH(labels, r'\|scratch_disk_type:%%DISK_TYPE%%\|') AND
    REGEXP_MATCH(labels, r'\|scratch_disk_size:%%DISK_SIZE%%\|') AND
    REGEXP_MATCH(labels, r'\|iodepth:%%IO_DEPTH%%\|')
GROUP BY
	machine_type,
	cloud
ORDER BY
  number ASC;
datasource.query_exec:
SELECT
	'',
	REGEXP_EXTRACT(labels, r'\|machine_type:(.*?)\|') AS machine_type,
	REGEXP_EXTRACT(labels, r'\|cloud:(.*?)\|') AS cloud,
	NTH(50, QUANTILES(value)) AS number

	[{{ dataset_name }}.{{ table_name }}]

	timestamp >= TIMESTAMP_TO_SEC(DATE_ADD(CURRENT_TIMESTAMP(), -3, 'MONTH')) AND
	product_name = 'PerfKitBenchmarker' AND
	test = 'block_storage_workload' AND
	metric = 'random_write:write:bandwidth' AND

    REGEXP_MATCH(labels, r'\|scratch_disk_size:500\|') AND
    REGEXP_MATCH(labels, r'\|iodepth:16\|')
GROUP BY
	machine_type,
	cloud
ORDER BY
  number ASC;
